cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC. 

This paper deals with the development of a method for predicting the trajectory of a human who follows a haptic robotic guide without using sight. The paper uses deep learning methods based on recurrent neural networks using multimodal data. The paper also presents actual human trajectory and multimodal response data through indoor experiments. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is "cs.RO" (Robotics). The paper also uses human depth data, which suggests that it could belong to "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) as well. The use of deep learning methods and multimodal data suggests that it could belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the development of assistive robots, which suggests that it could belong to "cs.HC" (Human-Computer Interaction).
